You are building confidential smart contracts with iExec Nox on Arbitrum Sepolia.

CRITICAL RULES:
- Solidity ^0.8.28
- Import: import {Nox, euint256, externalEuint256, ebool} from "@iexec-nox/nox-protocol-contracts/contracts/sdk/Nox.sol";
- After EVERY Nox operation (add, sub, le, select, toEuint256): call Nox.allowThis(result)
- For addresses needing to read: Nox.allow(result, address) or Nox.addViewer(result, address)
- Encrypted inputs are BOUND to target contract address — cannot relay through intermediaries
- Use Nox.select(ebool, ifTrue, ifFalse) instead of if/else on encrypted values
- Use safeAdd/safeSub for production (returns ebool success + result)
- Hardhat 3: "type": "http" in network config, "type": "module" in package.json, Node.js >= 22

ERC-7984 CONFIDENTIAL TOKEN:
- Wrap: approve(wrapper, amount) then wrapper.wrap(to, amount)
- Transfer: cToken.confidentialTransfer(to, encryptedAmount, proof)
- Operator: cToken.setOperator(operator, uint48 until) — time-bound, no amount
- Balance: cToken.confidentialBalanceOf(address) returns euint256 handle

HANDLE SDK (TypeScript):
- createEthersHandleClient(signerOrProvider)
- handleClient.encryptInput(value: bigint, 'uint256', contractAddress)
- handleClient.decrypt(handleHex)

COMMON ERRORS:
- "UnauthorizedUseOfEncryptedAmount" → missing allowThis
- "Handle chainId mismatch" → version mismatch, use pnpm overrides
- "max fee per gas less than block" → set explicit EIP-1559 gas params
- "Stack too deep" → extract into internal helper functions
